      "amount": "1/4 tsp",
      "notes": "to taste"
    },
    {
      "name": "bread",
      "amount": "1 small",
      "notes": "for serving"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 425°F (220°C).",
    "In a large bowl, combine the refried beans, onion, carrot, and Brussels sprouts.",
    "Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with yeast, salt, and black pepper. Toss to coat.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a baking sheet and roast for 25-30 minutes, or until the vegetables are tender and lightly caramelized.",
    "Meanwhile, slice the bread into small pieces and toast until lightly browned.",
    "To assemble the bowls, divide the roasted vegetable mixture among four plates or bowls.",
    "Top each bowl with toasted bread and serve immediately.",
    "Optional: garnish with chopped fresh herbs, such as parsley or chives."
  ],
